<a id="top"> </a><h1>One-year Assistant Professor, University of Toronto</h1>
<p>
The Institute for the History and Philosophy of Science and Technology 
invites applications for a one-year contractually-limited term 
appointment in the Philosophy of Science at the rank of Assistant 
Professor, effective July 1, 2012. Subject to a satisfactory review, the 
position will be renewed for one year.
</p>
<p> 
The successful candidate must demonstrate excellence in teaching and 
research and will be expected to teach undergraduate courses in the 
philosophy of science, science and society and science and values. The 
successful candidate should be engaged in research and is expected to 
teach one half course at the graduate level in the philosophy of science. 
Evidence of some background or interest in the history of science would 
be welcomed. The successful candidate should have a PhD. Salary will be 
commensurate with experience.
</p> 
<p>
Qualified candidates are invited to apply online by clicking on the link 
below. For submission guidelines, please visit: 
<a href="http://uoft.me/how-to-apply" rel="external">http://uoft.me/how-to-apply</a>. 
Please combine your application into one or two files. The online system 
can accommodate up to five attachments (10 MB) per profile. 
</p>
<p>
We will begin considering materials on June 28, 2012 and will continue 
until the post is filled. Complete applications will include cover 
letter; curriculum vitae; teaching statement, including outlines of 
proposed courses; and an article-length writing sample. All application 
materials should be submitted online. 
</p>
<p>
Three letters of reference should be sent under separate cover, 
preferably as signed PDF documents on letterhead to Craig Fraser at 
<a href="mailto:search.ihpst@utoronto.ca" rel="email">search.ihpst@utoronto.ca</a> 
(putting "Philosophy of Science" and the applicant's name in the subject 
line, please). 
</p>
